 <h2>The Perfect Baking Temperature and Timing</h2>
 <p>Getting the perfect crust is key in <strong>pizza baking</strong>. You need to focus on the oven temperature and timing. A well-preheated oven is crucial for a crispy crust and a well-cooked pizza.</p>
 <p>Preheating your oven to the right temperature is vital. For a classic New York-style pizza, aim for 500°F to 600°F. This high heat makes the crust crispy and golden brown. Use a pizza stone or baking steel to improve the crust's texture and flavor.</p>
 <h3>Optimal Baking Techniques</h3>
