 <h2>Common Pizza-Making Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
 <p>As I work on making the perfect New York-style pizza, I've learned to steer clear of common <em>pizza making mistakes</em>. One big error is overworking the dough, which makes the crust dense and tough. To fix this, mix and knead the dough just enough, then let it rest and rise.</p>
 <p>Another mistake is using the wrong cheese. For a true New York-style pizza, use high-quality mozzarella. It melts well and adds a creamy texture. Avoid low-moisture mozzarella to prevent a soggy crust and ensure balanced flavors.</p>
